annotationA: Obstructor-A, isoform A; Obstructor-A forms a core complex with chitin and the chitin modifying proteins serp and knk. This complex is required for assembly, maturation and preservation of the chitinous cuticles at the end of embryogenesis and probably throughout larval development
annotationB: Knickkopf is a GPI-anchorded protein, needed for chitin organisation in the cuticle and the tracheal system (tracheal cuticle, tube diameter regulation & gas filling)
